<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-12T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-12T23:00:00-05:00" n="983" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d983">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.79611 Pangborn-Herndon Flight/11:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Forbes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-13T13:00:00+09:00">April 13, 1931—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 13—5:17 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>51. Department’s 50, April 6 [<hi rend="italic">2</hi>], 7 p.m. Japanese
                            Government desires to know definitely route Pangborn plane will follow
                            before issuing permit.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Forbes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>